I"¶<h2 id="hex-editing">Hex Editing</h2>
<p>know where to edit, directly edit using hex editor.<br />
only allows in-place editing. No adding new bytes.<br />
But can rewrite padding bytes, dead code, or unused data.</p>

<p>LD_PRELOAD: specify libraries for the linker to load before.</p>

<h2 id="injecting-a-code-section">Injecting a code section</h2>

<p>By appending bytes to the end of the binary.<br />
Create a section header.<br />
Create a program header.<br />
Rename the section name in .shstrtab<br />
Call the injected code.</p>

<p>PT_NOTE header saft to overwrite.<br />
Need to change type to SHT_PROGBITS.</p>

<p>Injected code will run when the program starts.</p>

<h2 id="hijacking-got-entries">Hijacking GOT entries</h2>
<p>Replace GOT entry to replace a library call with an injected function.</p>

<p>Only work for library calls.<br />
directly modify direct call instructions.</p>

<p>Position Independent Executables (PIE)</p>
